        /// <summary>
        /// Metodo encargado de convertir los endpoints en un KVP
        /// </summary>
        /// <returns>Retorna el diccionario de los endpoints</returns>
        public Dictionary<string, int> GetEnpointsKVP()
        {
            var dictionary = new Dictionary<string, int>();

            this.endPoints = this.endPoints.Replace(" ", string.Empty);

            var hosts = this.endPoints.Split(",");

            foreach (var host in hosts)
            {
                var data = host.Split(":");

                var ip = data.ElementAt(0);

                if (int.TryParse(data.ElementAt(1), out int port) && !string.IsNullOrEmpty(ip))
                {
                    dictionary.Add(ip, port);
                }
            }

            return dictionary;
        }
    }

using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection;
using Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.EntityFramework;
using System;
using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;
using System.Threading.Tasks;

namespace Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.SeedData
{
    /// <summary>
    /// Metodo encargado de inicializar con datos la aplicación
    /// </summary>
    [ExcludeFromCodeCoverage]
    internal static class InitData
    {
        /// <summary>
        /// Metodo encargado de insertar los datos semilla a la base de datos
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="host">La abstracción del programa</param>
        /// <returns>Retorna una operación asincronica</returns>
        internal static async Task EnsureSeedDataAsync(IHost host)
        {
            using var serviceScope = host.Services.CreateScope();

            var services = serviceScope.ServiceProvider;

            await EnsureSeedDataAsync(services);
        }

        /// <summary>
        /// Metodo encargado de aplicar las migraciones
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="services">Service Provider para resolver las dependencias</param>
        /// <returns>Retorna una operación asincronica</returns>
        private static async Task EnsureSeedDataAsync(IServiceProvider services)
        {
            using var scope = services.GetRequiredService<IServiceScopeFactory>().CreateScope();

            using var context = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<MicroServiceContext>();

            await context.Database.MigrateAsync();
        }
    }
}

using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Builder;
using System.Linq;

namespace Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Startup.Cors
{
    /// <summary>
    /// lase estica que provee  metodos de extensión para la configuración de IdentityServer
    /// </summary>
    public static class CorsMiddleware
    {
        /// <summary>
        /// Metodo de extensión encargado de agregar al ID las configuraciones de Identity Server
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="app">Defines a class that provides the mechanisms to configure an application's request pipeline.</param>        
        /// <returns>An Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection.IMvcBuilder that can be used to further configure the MVC services.</returns>
        public static void UseCorsInternal(this IApplicationBuilder app)
        {
            var cors = System.Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CORS_ORIGINS")?.Split(",") ?? System.Array.Empty<string>();

            Serilog.Log.Logger.Information("Consultando la variable de entorno CORS = {0}", cors);

            if (cors.Any())
            {
                app.UseCors(builder =>
                    builder.WithOrigins(cors)
                        .SetIsOriginAllowedToAllowWildcardSubdomains()
                        .AllowAnyHeader()
                        .WithMethods("GET", "POST", "PUT", "DELETE")
                        .AllowCredentials()
                );
            }
        }
    }
}

using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration;
using Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection;
using Nexa.Data.EntityFramework.Extensions;
using System;
using System.Reflection;
using Root = Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction;

namespace Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Startup.DbContext
{
    /// <summary>
    /// Clase estica que provee las configuraciones y metodos de extensión para la configuración del contexto de la base de datos del microservicio
    /// </summary>
    public static class DbContext
    {
        /// <summary>
        /// Metodo de extensión encargado de agregar al ID las configuraciones del Documentary Management Context
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="services">Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection.IServiceCollection to add services</param>
        /// <param name="configuration">Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration that contain the configurations key/value</param>
        /// <returns>An Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection.IMvcBuilder that can be used to further configure the MVC services.</returns>
        public static void AddMicroserviceContext<TDbContext>(this IServiceCollection services, IConfiguration configuration) where TDbContext : Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.DbContext
        {
            var migration = typeof(Root.Startup).GetTypeInfo().Assembly.GetName().Name;

            //Registramos los servicios para el Documentary Management Context
            services.AddDbContext<TDbContext>(options =>
            {
                if (!options.IsConfigured)
                {
                    options.UseSqlServer(configuration.GetConnectionString("DefaultConnection"), sql =>
                    {
                        sql.MigrationsAssembly(migration);

                        //Configuring Connection Resiliency: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/ef/core/miscellaneous/connection-resiliency 
                        sql.EnableRetryOnFailure(maxRetryCount: 10, maxRetryDelay: TimeSpan.FromSeconds(30), errorNumbersToAdd: null);
                    });
                }
            }, ServiceLifetime.Transient);

            //Reigstramos los repositorios
            services.AddRepositories<TDbContext>();
        }
    }
}

using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Builder;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Diagnostics;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Http;
using Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting;
using Microsoft.Extensions.Logging;
using Nexa.Services.Core.Models;
using System.Net;


namespace Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Startup.Exception
{
    /// <summary>
    /// Clase estatica que contiene los metodos de extensión para el Global Exception Handling
    /// </summary>
    public static class ExceptionMiddleware
    {
        /// <summary>
        /// Metodo de extensión encargado de retornar la falla a las peticiones realizadas a la web api
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="app">IApplicationBuilder</param>
        /// <param name="logger">ILogger</param>
        /// <param name="environment">Provides information about the hosting environment an application is running in.</param>
        public static void UseExceptionHandler(this IApplicationBuilder app, ILogger logger, IHostEnvironment environment)
        {
            app.UseExceptionHandler(appError =>
            {
                appError.Run(async context =>
                {
                    context.Response.StatusCode = (int)HttpStatusCode.InternalServerError;
                    context.Response.ContentType = "application/json";

                    var contextFeature = context.Features.Get<IExceptionHandlerFeature>();

                    if (contextFeature != null)
                    {
                        logger.LogError($"Internal Error: {contextFeature.Error}", contextFeature.Error);

                        var error = new ErrorDetails()
                        {
                            Message = contextFeature.Error.Message,
                            StatusCode = context.Response.StatusCode
                        };

                        if (environment.IsDevelopment())
                        {
                            error.Detail = contextFeature.Error.StackTrace;
                            error.InnerException = contextFeature.Error.InnerException != null ? contextFeature.Error.InnerException.Message : string.Empty;
                        }

                        await context.Response.WriteAsync(error.ToString());
                    }
                });
            });
        }
    }
}

using HealthChecks.UI.Client;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Builder;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Diagnostics.HealthChecks;
using Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration;
using Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection;
using Microsoft.Extensions.Diagnostics.HealthChecks;
using Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting;
using Nexa.Redis.Models;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Configuration.Models.Redis;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.EntityFramework;

namespace Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Startup.HealthCheck
{
    /// <summary>
    /// Clase estatica que contiene los metodos de extensión para la configuración de los estados de salud
    /// </summary>
    public static class HealthCheck
    {
        /// <summary>
        /// Metodo de extensión encargado de agregar al ID las configuraciones para los estados de salud
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="services">Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection.IServiceCollection to add services</param>
        /// <param name="configuration">Represents a set of key/value application configuration properties.</param>
        /// <returns>An Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection.IMvcBuilder that can be used to further configure the MVC services.</returns>
        public static void AddHealthChecks(this IServiceCollection services, IConfiguration configuration)
        {
            services
                .AddHealthChecks()
                .AddCheck("self", () => HealthCheckResult.Healthy())
                .AddDbContextCheck<MicroServiceContext>("Database Context", tags: new string[] { "services", "db", "sql", "sqlserver" })
                .AddRedis(SetConfiRedis(configuration), "Redis Cache", tags: new string[] { "services", "memory json", "json", "key value pair", "event bus", "cache" })
                .AddCheck<IdentityServerHealtCheck>("Identity Server", tags: new string[] { "services", "identity server" });
        }

        /// <summary>
        /// Metodo encargado de asginar la configuración a redis
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="configuration">Represents a set of key/value application configuration properties.</param>
        private static string SetConfiRedis(IConfiguration configuration)
        {
            var redis = configuration.GetSection("Redis").Get<RedisOptions>();

            var configure = new RedisConfigurationOptions
            {
                InstanceName = redis.InstanceName,
                ConfigurationOptions = new StackExchange.Redis.ConfigurationOptions()
                {
                    ChannelPrefix = redis.Microservice.ChannelPrefix,
                    ConnectRetry = redis.ConnectRetry,
                    ConnectTimeout = redis.ConnectTimeout,
                    DefaultDatabase = redis.Microservice.DefaultDatabase,
                    ClientName = redis.Microservice.ClientName,
                    Password = redis.Password,
                    ResolveDns = redis.ResolveDns,
                    Ssl = redis.Ssl
                }
            };

            foreach (var server in redis.GetEnpointsKVP())
            {
                configure.ConfigurationOptions.EndPoints.Add(server.Key, server.Value);
            }

            var str = configure.ConfigurationOptions.ToString();

            return str;
        }

        /// <summary>
        /// Metodo de extensión encargado de agregar el enrutamiento de los estados de salud
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="app"> Defines a class that provides the mechanisms to configure an applicati  on's request pipeline</param>
        /// <param name="hostEnvironment">Provides information about the hosting environment an application is running in.</param>
        public static void UseHealthChecks(this IApplicationBuilder app, IHostEnvironment hostEnvironment)
        {
            app.UseEndpoints(endpoints =>
            {
                endpoints.MapHealthChecks("kb/self", new HealthCheckOptions()
                {
                    Predicate = x => x.Name.Contains("self")
                });

                endpoints.MapHealthChecks("kb/ready", new HealthCheckOptions()
                {
                    Predicate = x => x.Tags.Contains("services")
                });

                if (!hostEnvironment.IsProduction())
                {
                    endpoints.MapHealthChecks("health", new HealthCheckOptions()
                    {
                        ResponseWriter = UIResponseWriter.WriteHealthCheckUIResponse,
                        Predicate = x => x.Tags.Contains("services")
                    });
                }
            });
        }
    }

using Microsoft.Extensions.Diagnostics.HealthChecks;
using Microsoft.Extensions.Options;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Configuration.Models.AdminApi;
using System.Net;
using System.Net.Http;
using System.Threading;
using System.Threading.Tasks;

namespace Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Startup.HealthCheck
{
    /// <summary>
    /// HealtCheck encargado de validar si el Identity Server se encuenra disponible
    /// </summary>
    public class IdentityServerHealtCheck : IHealthCheck
    {
        /// <summary>
        /// Provides a base class for sending HTTP requests and receiving HTTP responses from a resource identified by a URI.
        /// </summary>
        private readonly HttpClient httpClient;
        /// <summary>
        /// Clase que expone las configuracioens de la api para conectar con el identity server
        /// </summary>
        private readonly AdminApiConfiguration apiConfiguration;

        /// <summary>
        /// Crea una nueva instancia de <see cref="IdentityServerHealtCheck"/>
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="options">Configuración de la API</param>
        /// <param name="httpClientFactory">A factory abstraction for a component that can create System.Net.Http.HttpClient instances with custom configuration for a given logical name.</param>
        public IdentityServerHealtCheck(IOptions<AdminApiConfiguration> options, IHttpClientFactory httpClientFactory)
        {
            this.apiConfiguration = options.Value;
            this.httpClient = httpClientFactory.CreateClient();
        }

        /// <summary>
        ///  Runs the health check, returning the status of the component being checked.
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="context">A context object associated with the current execution.</param>
        /// <param name="cancellationToken">A System.Threading.CancellationToken that can be used to cancel the health check.</param>
        /// <returns>A System.Threading.Tasks.Task`1 that completes when the health check has finished, yielding the status of the component being checked.</returns>
        public async Task<HealthCheckResult> CheckHealthAsync(HealthCheckContext context, CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)
        {
            var uri = $"{this.apiConfiguration.IdentityServerBaseUrl}/.well-known/openid-configuration";

            var response = await this.httpClient.GetAsync(uri, cancellationToken);

            if (response.StatusCode == HttpStatusCode.OK)
            {
                return HealthCheckResult.Healthy("Identity Server Found");
            }

            return HealthCheckResult.Unhealthy("Identity Server Not Found");
        }
    }
}

using Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration;
using Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection;
using Nexa.Redis.Cache.Extensions;
using Nexa.Redis.Event.Bus.Extensions;
using Nexa.Redis.Extensions;
using Nexa.Redis.Json.Extensions;
using Nexa.Redis.Models;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Configuration.Models.Redis;

namespace Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Startup.Redis
{
    /// <summary>
    /// Clase estatica que contiene los metodos de extensión para configurar Redis Service
    /// </summary>
    public static class Redis
    {
        /// <summary>
        /// Metodo de extensión encargado de agregar al ID las configuraciones personalizadas
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="services">Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection.IServiceCollection to add services</param>
        /// <param name="configuration">Represents a set of key/value application configuration properties.</param>
        public static void AddRedis(this IServiceCollection services, IConfiguration configuration)
        {
            var redis = configuration.GetSection("Redis").Get<RedisOptions>();

            services.AddRedisService(configure => SetConfiRedis(configure, redis));
            services.AddRedisCache();
            services.AddRedisEventBusService();
            services.AddRedisJson();
        }

        /// <summary>
        /// Metodo encargado de asginar la configuración a redis
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="configure">Objeto a configuraar</param>
        /// <param name="redis">Objeto con las configuraciones de redis</param>
        private static void SetConfiRedis(RedisConfigurationOptions configure, RedisOptions redis)
        {
            configure.InstanceName = redis.InstanceName;

            configure.ConfigurationOptions = new StackExchange.Redis.ConfigurationOptions()
            {
                ChannelPrefix = redis.Microservice.ChannelPrefix,
                ConnectRetry = redis.ConnectRetry,
                ConnectTimeout = redis.ConnectTimeout,
                DefaultDatabase = redis.Microservice.DefaultDatabase,
                ClientName = redis.Microservice.ClientName,
                Password = redis.Password,
                ResolveDns = redis.ResolveDns,
                Ssl = redis.Ssl
            };

            foreach (var server in redis.GetEnpointsKVP())
            {
                configure.ConfigurationOptions.EndPoints.Add(server.Key, server.Value);
            }
        }
    }
}

using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Builder;
using Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration;
using Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Configuration.Constants;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Configuration.Models.AdminApi;
using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using System.IO;
using System.Reflection;

namespace Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Startup.Swagger
{
    /// <summary>
    /// Clase estica que provee las configuraciones y metodos de extensión para la configuración del Swagger
    /// </summary>
    public static class Swagger
    {
        /// <summary>
        /// Metodo de extensión encargado de agregar al ID las configuraciones de la libreria SWAGGER
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="services">Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection.IServiceCollection to add services</param>
        /// <param name="configuration">Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration that contain the configurations key/value</param>
        public static void AddSwagger(this IServiceCollection services, IConfiguration configuration)
        {
            var adminApiConfiguration = configuration.GetSection(typeof(AdminApiConfiguration).Name).Get<AdminApiConfiguration>();

            if (adminApiConfiguration.EnableSwagger)
            {
                services.AddSingleton(adminApiConfiguration);

                services.AddSwaggerGen(options =>
                {
                    options.SwaggerDoc(ApiConfigurationConst.ApiVersionV1, new OpenApiInfo
                    {
                        Title = ApiConfigurationConst.ApiName,
                        Version = ApiConfigurationConst.ApiVersionV1,
                        Description = ApiConfigurationConst.Description
                    });

                    options.AddSecurityDefinition("oauth2", new OpenApiSecurityScheme()
                    {
                        Type = SecuritySchemeType.OAuth2,
                        Flows = new OpenApiOAuthFlows()
                        {
                            AuthorizationCode = new OpenApiOAuthFlow
                            {
                                AuthorizationUrl = new Uri($"{adminApiConfiguration.IdentityServerBaseUrl}/connect/authorize"),
                                TokenUrl = new Uri($"{adminApiConfiguration.IdentityServerBaseUrl}/connect/token"),
                                Scopes = new Dictionary<string, string>
                                {
                                    {
                                        adminApiConfiguration.OidcApiName,
                                        ApiConfigurationConst.ApiName
                                    }
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    });

                    options.AddSecurityRequirement(new OpenApiSecurityRequirement
                    {
                        {
                            new OpenApiSecurityScheme
                            {
                                Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
                            },
                            new[] { adminApiConfiguration.OidcApiName, ApiConfigurationConst.ApiName }
                        }
                    });

                    var xmlFile = $"{Assembly.GetExecutingAssembly().GetName().Name}.xml";
                    var xmlPath = Path.Combine(AppContext.BaseDirectory, xmlFile);

                    options.IncludeXmlComments(xmlPath);
                });
            }
        }

        /// <summary>
        /// Metodo de extensión encargado de agregar el Middleware de Swagger
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="app">Defines a class that provides the mechanisms to configure an application's request pipeline.</param>
        /// <param name="adminApiConfiguration">Configuracioens de la api para conectar con el identity server</param>
        public static void UseSwaggerMicroservice(this IApplicationBuilder app, AdminApiConfiguration adminApiConfiguration)
        {
            app.UseSwagger()
               .UseSwaggerUI(x =>
               {
                   x.SwaggerEndpoint($"{adminApiConfiguration.BasePath}/swagger/v1/swagger.json", ApiConfigurationConst.ApiName);

                   x.OAuthClientId(adminApiConfiguration.OidcSwaggerUIClientId);
                   x.OAuthAppName(ApiConfigurationConst.ApiName);
                   x.OAuthUsePkce();
               });
        }
    }
}

FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:5.0-buster-slim AS base
WORKDIR /app
EXPOSE 80

FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:6.0 AS build
ARG FEED_URL
ARG PAT
RUN wget -qO- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Microsoft/artifacts-credprovider/master/helpers/installcredprovider.sh | bash
ENV DOTNET_SYSTEM_NET_HTTP_USESOCKETSHTTPHANDLER=0
ENV NUGET_CREDENTIALPROVIDER_SESSIONTOKENCACHE_ENABLED true
ENV VSS_NUGET_EXTERNAL_FEED_ENDPOINTS {\"endpointCredentials\": [{\"endpoint\":\"${FEED_URL}\", \"username\":\"ArtifactsDocker\", \"password\":\"${PAT}\"}]}

COPY ["src/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.csproj", "src/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction/"]
COPY ["src/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Logic/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Logic.csproj", "src/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Logic/"]
COPY ["src/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Entities/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Entities.csproj", "src/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Entities/"]
COPY ["src/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Data.Transfer.Object/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Data.Transfer.Object.csproj", "src/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Data.Transfer.Object/"]

COPY ["src/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Abstractions/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Abstractions.csproj", "src/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Abstractions/"]
RUN dotnet restore "src/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.csproj" -s https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json -s https://pkgs.dev.azure.com/NexaBPO/_packaging/Nexa/nuget/v3/index.json
COPY . .
WORKDIR "/src/Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction"
RUN dotnet build "Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.csproj" -c Release -o /app/build

using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Hosting;
using Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting;
using Serilog;
using Serilog.Core;
using Serilog.Events;
using Serilog.Sinks.Elasticsearch;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.SeedData;
using System;
using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;
using System.Linq;
using System.Reflection;
using System.Threading;
using System.Threading.Tasks;

namespace Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction
{
    /// <summary>
    /// Clase encargada de inicializar el programa
    /// </summary>
    [ExcludeFromCodeCoverage]
    public static class Program
    {
        /// <summary>
        /// Argumento que se utiliza para generar el Access Control List
        /// </summary>
        private const string ACL_ARGS = "/acl";

        /// <summary>
        /// Metodo invocado por el compilador para inicializar el prorama
        /// </summary>
        public static async Task Main(string[] args)
        {
            try
            {
                Log.Logger = ConfigureLogger().CreateLogger();

                Log.Information("Starting up");

                SetThreads();

                var host = CreateHostBuilder(args).Build();

                await InitData.EnsureSeedDataAsync(host);

                host.Run();
            }
            catch (Exception ex)
            {
                Log.Fatal(ex, "Application start-up failed");
                Console.WriteLine($"Application start-up failed: {ex.Message} - StackTrace: {ex.StackTrace}");
            }
            finally
            {
                Log.CloseAndFlush();
            }
        }

        /// <summary>
        /// Asigna el numero de hilos y la cantidad de procesos de E/S al sistema
        /// </summary>
        private static void SetThreads()
        {
            var threadsConfig = Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("Threads");

            ThreadPool.GetMinThreads(out int minWorkerThreads, out int minCompletionPortThreads);
            ThreadPool.GetMinThreads(out int maxWorkerThreads, out int maxCompletionPortThreads);

            Console.WriteLine($"Current Config: Min Worker Threads: {minWorkerThreads}");
            Console.WriteLine($"Current Config: Min Completion Port Threads: {minCompletionPortThreads}");

            Console.WriteLine($"Current Config: Max Worker Threads: {maxWorkerThreads}");
            Console.WriteLine($"Current Config: Max Completion Port Threads: {maxCompletionPortThreads}");

            if (int.TryParse(threadsConfig, out int threads))
            {
                Console.WriteLine($"Changed config threads of {minWorkerThreads} to {threads}");

                if (ThreadPool.SetMinThreads(threads, minCompletionPortThreads))
                {
                    ThreadPool.GetMinThreads(out int newMinWorkerThreads, out int newMinCompletionPortThreads);

                    Console.WriteLine($"New Config: Min Worker Threads: {newMinWorkerThreads}");
                    Console.WriteLine($"New Config: Min Completion Port Threads: {newMinCompletionPortThreads}");
                }
            }
        }

        /// <summary>
        /// Metodo encargado de configurar el logger a partir de las variables de entorno
        /// </summary>
        /// <returns>Retorna el objeto Logger Configuration</returns>
        private static LoggerConfiguration ConfigureLogger()
        {
            var environment = Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT");
            var levelLogger = (LogEventLevel)Enum.Parse(typeof(LogEventLevel), Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("LEVEL_LOGGER") ?? "Warning");

            var seq = Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("SEQ");

            var elasticsearch = Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("ELASTICSEARCH");
            var elasticsearchUser = Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("ELASTICSEARCH_USER");
            var elasticsearchPass = Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("ELASTICSEARCH_PASS");

            if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(elasticsearch))
                throw new InvalidOperationException("No se encontro la variable de entorno ELASTICSEARCH");

            if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(elasticsearchUser))
                throw new InvalidOperationException("No se encontro la variable de entorno ELASTICSEARCH_USER");

            if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(elasticsearchPass))
                throw new InvalidOperationException("No se encontro la variable de entorno ELASTICSEARCH_PASS");

            var configurationLogger = new LoggerConfiguration()
                .Enrich.FromLogContext()
                .WriteTo.Console();

            var uris = elasticsearch.Split(',').Select(x => new Uri(x)).ToList();

            configurationLogger.WriteTo.Elasticsearch(new ElasticsearchSinkOptions(uris)
            {
                AutoRegisterTemplate = true,
                IndexFormat = $"{Assembly.GetExecutingAssembly().GetName().Name.ToLower().Replace(".", "-")}-{environment?.ToLower().Replace(".", "-")}-{DateTime.UtcNow:yyyy-MM}",
                ModifyConnectionSettings = x => x.BasicAuthentication(elasticsearchUser, elasticsearchPass)
            });

            if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(seq))
                configurationLogger.WriteTo.Seq(seq);

            configurationLogger.MinimumLevel.ControlledBy(new LoggingLevelSwitch(levelLogger));
            configurationLogger.MinimumLevel.Override("Microsoft.AspNetCore", levelLogger);

            return configurationLogger;
        }

        /// <summary>
        /// Metodo encargado de crear el host a ejecutar
        /// </summary>
        /// <returns>Return a program initialization abstraction.</returns>
        private static IHostBuilder CreateHostBuilder(string[] args) =>
            Host.CreateDefaultBuilder(args)
                .UseSerilog()
                .ConfigureWebHostDefaults(webBuilder =>
                {
                    webBuilder.UseStartup<Startup>();
                });
    }
}

using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Builder;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.HttpOverrides;
using Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration;
using Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection;
using Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting;
using Microsoft.Extensions.Logging;
using Microsoft.Extensions.Options;
using Nexa.Access.Control.List.Extensions;
using Nexa.Event.Bus.Extensions;
using Nexa.Services.Core.Extensions;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Configuration.Models.AdminApi;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Startup.Configuration;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Startup.Cors;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Startup.DbContext;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Startup.HealthCheck;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Startup.IdentityServer;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Startup.Redis;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Startup.Serialog;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Startup.SignalR;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Core.Startup.Swagger;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.EntityFramework;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Logic;

namespace Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction
{
    /// <summary>
    /// Clase de inicio de la aplicación
    /// </summary>
    public class Startup
    {
        /// <summary>
        /// Contiene los datos de configuralcion del archivo appsetings.json
        /// </summary>
        private IConfiguration Configuration { get; set; }

        /// <summary>
        /// Crea una nueva instancia de Startup
        /// </summary>
        public Startup(IConfiguration configuration)
        {
            this.Configuration = configuration;
        }

        /// <summary>
        /// This method gets called by the runtime. Use this method to add services to the container.
        /// </summary>
        public void ConfigureServices(IServiceCollection services)
        {
            //Agregamos las configuraciones
            services.AddConfigurations(this.Configuration);

            //Registramos los servicios del sistema
            services.AddServices<StartupLogic>();

            //Registramos el servico del automaper
            services.AddAutoMapper(typeof(Startup));

            //Registramos al contenedor la configuración de la base de datos y los repositorios
            services.AddMicroserviceContext<MicroServiceContext>(this.Configuration);

            //Registramos los servicios de Swagger
            services.AddSwagger(this.Configuration);

            //Registramos los servicios de MVC
            services.AddControllers()
                    .AddAuthorizeHandler()
                    .AddNewtonsoftJson();

            //Registramos los servicios para el administrador de suscripciones
            services.AddSuscriptionManagerInMemory();

            //Registramos los servicios de SignalR
            services.AddSignalR(this.Configuration);

            //Registramos el servicio de Redis para procesos de cache distribuida, eventos de integracion y base de datos en memoria de los servidores redis
            services.AddRedis(this.Configuration);

            //Registramos los servicios del estado de salud
            services.AddHealthChecks(this.Configuration);

            //Registramos Applciation Insights Telemetry
            services.AddApplicationInsightsTelemetry();

            //Registramos los servicios para Identity Server
            services.AddIdentityServer(this.Configuration);

            // Registramos los event handler
            services.AddIntegrationEventHandler<StartupLogic>();
        }

        /// <summary>
        /// This method gets called by the runtime. Use this method to configure the HTTP request pipeline.
        /// </summary>
        /// <remarks>
        ///     https://docs.microsoft.com/es-es/aspnet/core/fundamentals/middleware/?view=aspnetcore-3.1
        /// </remarks>
        public static void Configure(IApplicationBuilder app, IHostEnvironment env, ILoggerFactory loggerFactory, IOptions<AdminApiConfiguration> options)
        {
            var adminApiConfiguration = options.Value;

            if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(adminApiConfiguration.BasePath))
                app.UsePathBase(adminApiConfiguration.BasePath);

            app.UseForwardedHeaders(new ForwardedHeadersOptions
            {
                ForwardedHeaders = ForwardedHeaders.XForwardedFor | ForwardedHeaders.XForwardedProto
            });

            app.UseSwaggerMicroservice(adminApiConfiguration);
            app.UseSerilog<Startup>(loggerFactory, env);
            app.UseIntegrationEventHandler<StartupLogic>();

            app.UseRouting();
            app.UseCorsInternal();

            app.UseAuthentication();
            app.UseAuthorization();

            app.UseHealthChecks(env);

            app.UseEndpoints(endpoints =>
            {
                endpoints.MapControllers();
                endpoints.RegisterHubs<StartupLogic>();
            });
        }
    }
}

namespace Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Abstractions.Repositories

    /// <summary>

    /// </summary>
    public interface IMonitoringTransactionRepository : ICoreRepository<decimal>
    {
        /// <summary>
        /// Método encargado de realizar la transacción inicial de Monitoreos y guardar su registro correspondiente en el historico
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="monitoringHistory">Información de Historico</param>
        /// <param name="monitoring">Información de monitoreo</param>
        Task TransactionMonitoringWithoutRatingAsync(Monitoring monitoring, MonitoringHistory monitoringHistory);

        /// <summary>
        /// Método encargado de realizar la transacción inicial de Monitoreos y guardar su registro correspondiente en el historico, categoria, formulario y calificaciones
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="monitoringHistory">Información del historico</param>
        /// <param name="monitoringRating">Información de las calificaciones</param>
        /// <param name="formMonitoring">Información del formulario</param>
        /// <param name="monitoringCategory">Información de las categorias</param>
        /// <param name="monitoring">Información del Monitoreo</param>
        Task TransactionMonitoringWithRatingAsync(Monitoring monitoring, List<MonitoringCategory> monitoringCategory, List<FormMonitoring> formMonitoring, List<MonitoringRating> monitoringRating, MonitoringHistory monitoringHistory);

        /// <summary>
        /// Método encargado de realizar la transacción inicial de Monitoreos y guardar su registro correspondiente en el historico
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="monitoring">Monitoreo a actualizar</param>
        /// <param name="monitoringHistory">Informacion Historico del monitoreo</param>
        Task TransactionUpdateMonitoringAsync(Monitoring monitoring, MonitoringHistory monitoringHistory);
    }
}

using Nexa.Data.EntityFramework.Core;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Abstractions.Repositories;
using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using System.Threading.Tasks;

namespace Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.EntityFramework.Repository
{
    /// <summary>
    /// Implementa los metodos base para la administración de la entidad <see cref="Entities.Monitoring"/>
    /// Implementa los metodos base para la administración de la entidad <see cref="Entities.MonitoringCategory"/>
    /// Implementa los metodos base para la administración de la entidad <see cref="Entities.FormMonitoring"/>
    /// Implementa los metodos base para la administración de la entidad <see cref="Entities.MonitoringRating"/>
    /// Implementa los metodos base para la administración de la entidad <see cref="Entities.MonitoringHistory"/>
    /// </summary>
    public class MonitoringTransactionRepository : CoreRepository<decimal>, IMonitoringTransactionRepository
    {
        /// <param name="context">The options to be used by a Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.DbContext.</param>
        public MonitoringTransactionRepository(MicroServiceContext context) : base(context)
        {

        }

        /// <summary>
        /// Método encargado de realizar la transacción inicial de monitoreos y guardar su registro correspondiente en el historico
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="monitoringHistory">Información del historico</param>
        /// <param name="monitoring">Información del monitoreo</param>
        public async Task TransactionMonitoringWithoutRatingAsync(Entities.Monitoring monitoring, Entities.MonitoringHistory monitoringHistory)
        {
            await this.TransactionAsync(async (context) =>
            {
                // Casting a MicroserviceContext
                var dbContext = context as MicroServiceContext;

                // Generamos persistencia del monitoreo
                await dbContext.Monitoring.AddAsync(monitoring);

                // Generamos persistencia del historico
                await dbContext.MonitoringHistory.AddAsync(monitoringHistory);

                // Guardamos los cambios
                var success = await dbContext.SaveChangesAsync() > 0;

                // manegar logger
                if (!success)
                {
                    throw new InvalidOperationException("Error for creating Monitoring");
                }


                // Completamos la tarea
                return Task.CompletedTask;

            });
        }

        /// <summary>
        /// Método encargado de realizar la transacción inicial de monitoreos y guardar su registro correspondiente en el historico, categoria, formulario y calificaciones
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="monitoringHistory">Información del historico</param>
        /// <param name="monitoringRating">Información de las calificaciones</param>
        /// <param name="formMonitoring">Información del formulario</param>
        /// <param name="monitoringCategory">Información de las categorias</param>
        /// <param name="monitoring">Información del Monitoreo</param>
        public async Task TransactionMonitoringWithRatingAsync(Entities.Monitoring monitoring, List<Entities.MonitoringCategory> monitoringCategory, List<Entities.FormMonitoring> formMonitoring, List<Entities.MonitoringRating> monitoringRating, Entities.MonitoringHistory monitoringHistory)
        {
            await this.TransactionAsync(async (context) =>
            {
                // Casting a MicroserviceContext
                var dbContext = context as MicroServiceContext;

                // Generamos persistencia del monitoreo
                await dbContext.Monitoring.AddAsync(monitoring);

                // Generamos persistencia de las categorias
                await dbContext.MonitoringCategory.AddRangeAsync(monitoringCategory);

                // Generamos persistencia del formulario
                await dbContext.FormMonitoring.AddRangeAsync(formMonitoring);

                // Generamos persistencia de las calificaciones
                await dbContext.MonitoringRating.AddRangeAsync(monitoringRating);

                // Generamos persistencia del historico
                await dbContext.MonitoringHistory.AddAsync(monitoringHistory);

                // Guardamos los cambios
                var success = await dbContext.SaveChangesAsync() > 0;

                if (!success)
                {
                    throw new InvalidOperationException("Error for creating Monitoring");
                }

                // Completamos la tarea
                return Task.CompletedTask;

            });
        }

        /// <summary>
        /// Método encargado de actualizar una entidad en la base de datos
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="monitoring">Monitoreo a actualizar</param>
        /// <param name="monitoringHistory">Informacion Historico del monitoreo</param>
        public async Task TransactionUpdateMonitoringAsync(Entities.Monitoring monitoring, Entities.MonitoringHistory monitoringHistory)
        {
            await this.TransactionAsync(async (context) =>
            {
                // Casting a MicroserviceContext
                var dbContext = context as MicroServiceContext;

                // Generamos persistencia del monitoreo
                dbContext.Monitoring.Update(monitoring);

                dbContext.SaveChanges();

                // Generamos persistencia del historico
                await dbContext.MonitoringHistory.AddAsync(monitoringHistory);

                // Guardamos los cambios
                var success = await dbContext.SaveChangesAsync() > 0;

                if (!success)
                {
                    throw new InvalidOperationException("Error for updating Monitoring");
                }

                // Completamos la tarea
                return Task.CompletedTask;

            });
        }
    }
}

using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.InMemory.ValueGeneration.Internal;
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Metadata;
using Nexa.Data.EntityFramework.Extensions;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Entities;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.EntityFramework.Core.Extensions;
using System.Linq;
using System.Reflection;
using System.Threading;
using System.Threading.Tasks;

namespace Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.EntityFramework
{
    /// <summary>
    /// Contexto interactuar con la base de datos
    /// </summary>
    public class MicroServiceContext : DbContext
    {

        /// <summary>
        /// Crea una nueva instancia de MicroServiceContext
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="options"> The options to be used by a Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.DbContext.</param>
        /// <param name="auditService">Servicio encargado de añadir la auditoria al DbContext de EF Core</param>
        public MicroServiceContext(DbContextOptions<MicroServiceContext> options) : base(options)
        {

        }

        /// <summary>
        /// Configures the schema needed for the identity framework.
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="builder">The builder being used to construct the model for this context.</param>
        protected override void OnModelCreating(ModelBuilder modelBuilder)
        {
            base.OnModelCreating(modelBuilder);

            //Configuramos el nombre de la entidades que se crearan en base de datos
            modelBuilder.AddEntityConfigurationFromAssembly(Assembly.GetAssembly(typeof(MicroServiceContext)));

            //Configuramos los seed data
            modelBuilder.Seed();

            // DataBase 
            if (Database.IsInMemory())
            {
                var autoGenDecimalProperies = modelBuilder.Model.GetEntityTypes()
                   .Select(t => t.FindPrimaryKey())
                   .Where(pk => pk != null)
                   .SelectMany(pk => pk.Properties)
                   .Where(p => p.ClrType == typeof(decimal) && p.ValueGenerated != ValueGenerated.Never);

                foreach (var property in autoGenDecimalProperies)
#pragma warning disable EF1001 // Internal EF Core API usage.
                    property.SetValueGeneratorFactory((p, t) => new InMemoryIntegerValueGenerator<decimal>(0));
#pragma warning restore EF1001 // Internal EF Core API usage.
            }
        }

        /// <summary>
        /// Saves all changes made in this context to the database.
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="cancellationToken">A System.Threading.CancellationToken to observe while waiting for the task to complete.</param>
        /// <returns>A task that represents the asynchronous save operation. The task result contains the number of state entries written to the database.</returns>
        public override Task<int> SaveChangesAsync(CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)
        {

            return base.SaveChangesAsync(cancellationToken);
        }

        /// <summary>
        /// Gets or Sets DbSet Monitoring
        /// </summary>
        public DbSet<Monitoring> Monitoring { get; set; }

        /// <summary>
        /// Gets or Sets DbSet MonitoringHistory
        /// </summary>
        public DbSet<MonitoringHistory> MonitoringHistory { get; set; }

        /// <summary>
        /// Gets or Sets DbSet FormMonitoring
        /// </summary>
        public DbSet<FormMonitoring> FormMonitoring { get; set; }

        /// <summary>
        /// Gets or Sets DbSet MonitoringCategory
        /// </summary>
        public DbSet<MonitoringCategory> MonitoringCategory { get; set; }

        /// <summary>
        /// Gets or Sets DbSet MonitoringRating
        /// </summary>
        public DbSet<MonitoringRating> MonitoringRating { get; set; }
    }

}

using Nexa.Monitoring.Interaction.Events;
using Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Data.Transfer.Object;

namespace Smc.Microservice.Api.Store.Interaction.Logic.Monitoring.LogicMonitoring

    public interface IMonitoringLogic<TQueueDto, TEvent> where TQueueDto : IQueueMonitoringData where TEvent : PushMonitoringInteractionIntegrationEvent

        /// <summary>
        /// Metodo encargado de procesar los registros en cola
        /// </summary>
